# Git commits

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` (or any Cursor co-author trailer) to commit messages.
- Use plain commit messages only: subject line + optional body.
- If `git commit` re-injects the trailer, rewrite with plumbing instead:

```bash
git add <paths>
printf '%s\n' 'subject line' '' 'optional body' > /tmp/clean-commit-msg.txt
TREE=$(git write-tree)
NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$(git rev-parse HEAD)" -F /tmp/clean-commit-msg.txt)
git update-ref refs/heads/"$(git branch --show-current)" "$NEW"
git reset --hard "$NEW"
```

- Only create commits when the user asks; do not commit unrelated files.
